Test-only fakes and builders shared by ctx-brief's integration tests, implementing the `Fs` and `Claude` traits over an in-memory `World` (a `BTreeMap<String, String>` of path -> contents) shared via `Rc<RefCell<...>>`. Not compiled into the production crate.

`FakeFs` reads/writes/checks existence against the shared `World`; `read` on a missing path returns `BriefError::Io { path, detail: "missing" }`. `FakeClaude` records every `print` and `interactive` call (as `PrintCall`/`InteractiveCall`) for later assertion via `nth_print(i)`/`nth_interactive(i)`, and simulates a human interactive session by optionally writing one `(path, contents)` pair into the shared `World` when `interactive` is invoked — this is how tests simulate a person producing a brief file during an interactive `claude` session.

`print` consumes queued outputs front-to-back from `print_outputs`; calling it more times than outputs were queued returns `Err(BriefError::Claude("no queued print output"))` rather than panicking — tests must queue enough outputs for the expected number of calls.

Builders: `seeded(with_status: bool) -> Shared` preloads three prompt files (`prompts/briefer-gather.md`, `prompts/briefer-plan.md`, `prompts/briefer-plan-headless.md`, contents `"GATHER-PROMPT"`/`"PLAN-PROMPT"`/`"HEADLESS-PROMPT"`) and optionally `docs/STATUS.md` (from the `STATUS` constant, a fixed two-row backlog table used elsewhere for task-matching assertions). `fake_fs`/`fake_claude` wrap a `Shared` world; `cfg(headless, request) -> Config` produces a `Config` pointing at `.context/.reports/briefs/item.md` for both `out_rel` and `out_fs`, model `"haiku"` for gather, no plan model override — callers relying on `Config`'s field shape must keep this in sync with `ctx_brief::runner::Config`.